race.comment: PENNED (11) comes through a solid Kalgoorlie campaign where he wasn't beaten far over 1200m in a much stronger race. Freshened coming into this, but maps for a perfect run under Tsang, meaning he'll carry no weight. Everything points to a forward showing. SUPPORTIVE (3) has been going around in much stronger company at Belmont recently. Happy to overlook his most recent form and the wide barrier is no issue with his racing pattern. Hasn't won for a while but this presents as a brilliant opportunity to end the drought. SABINO (9) held on to score in a photo finish at Albany 20 days ago and turned in a good figure in the process. Can sit handy once again from the draw and a repeat effort will see him hard to hold out. OREGON HIKER (2) may need the run but he has a few ratings from his last campaign that can see him feature in this. FIRST LAW (5) will appreciate this easier company today and can improve third-up.
